ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Take this class if it is required for your major. If you are good with numbers then this class will be a piece of cake.
Take it if you have to or you love not particularly difficult, but definitely drawn-out and dynamic chemistry problems. Don't take it if it's not for your major.
Yes, I recommend it for anyone interested in chemistry, the environment, or geology.
The chemistry itself was interesting, but the classes were boring. Mostly psets.
This is acid-base equilibrium on steroids. Its pretty dry and tedious but also pretty easy. Take it if you must, but don't otherwise.
Absolutely. If you think it sounds interesting, take it.
It was an ok class. Lots of material is covered, but if you keep up and go to class everyday, you will be fine. Tests are open book.
I would only recommend the class to a fellow student if they were required to take it for a major. Otherwise I would recommend that they not take it.
If you have to take this course you will take it. If you don't need it I wouldn't take it. Some of the material is interesting but most of it seems quite repetitive.
